p: The identification of the chemical constituents of the EO was deconvoluted using AMDIS software (NIST, Gaithersburg, MD, USA; Wiley, Hoboken, NJ, USA) and identified by its retention indices (relative to n-alkanes C 8-C 22), mass spectrum matching to authentic standards (when available), the Wiley spectral library collection, and the NSIT library database.
